 eating.6. Keep healthy snacks available When you have healthy snacks available, your chance of choosing a healthy snack goes up considerably.  Bring one along in your backpack or pick one up conveniently at one of our UNT retail locations. 7. Only eat when you are hungry Be in tune with your body and recognize the difference between hunger and thirst. Also, just because food is free, it does not mean you have to eat it. Overeating and eating when you are not hungry will lead to weight gain.8. Be purposeful of when you are eating Being purposeful while choosing and eating meals will add to your enjoyment of the meal and help you make healthier food choices. 9. Manage your stress in a healthy wayThis will help prevent emotional eating and keep you feeling healthier, energized, and ready for school.10. Avoid fad diets  If you are looking to lose weight, research shows that the best way to lose weight in a healthy way is to aim for eating a balanced diet and to exercise regularly. Follow Us Tweets by @UNTdining Like Us University of North Texas Dining © 2017 A Mopro Website Back to Top 